Package: covid19nytimes
Title: Pulls the covid-19 data from the New York Times Public Data Source
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: 
    person(given = "Jarrett",
           family = "Byrnes",
           role = c("aut", "cre"),
           email = "jarrett.byrnes@umb.edu",
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-9791-9472"))
Description: This package access the NY Times Covid-19 county-level data for the US, described in https://www.nytimes.com/article/coronavirus-county-data-us.html and available at https://github.com/nytimes/covid-19-data. It then returns the data in a tidy data format accordin to the covid19R data specification.
License: See https://github.com/nytimes/covid-19-data/blob/master/LICENSE
Suggests: 
    testthat,
    ggplot2,
    knitr,
    rmarkdown
Depends:
  R (>= 3.0.2)
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
Roxygen: list(markdown = TRUE)
RoxygenNote: 7.1.0
URL: https://github.com/Covid19R/covid19nytimes
